-broken-h-1b-visa-process/\" target=\"_blank\">https://crane.house.gov/2026/04/22/rep-crane-introduces-legislation-to-pause-and-reform-the-broken-h-1b-visa-process/</a></p>\n<p>Make sure to contact your representatives and let them know you support this bill. Probably gonna be an uphill battle but we all see how so many areas of the country have been overrun by Indians.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 31, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsL4AWzU", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 16, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8602164, "raw_content": "When the Sun Reminds Us Who\u2019s in Charge\nWe\u2019ve come to rely on satellites for almost everything: directions, banking, weather, communications.\n\nBut all of it rests on a quiet assumption - that the Sun will behave itself.\n\nHistory suggests that\u2019s a risky bet.\n\nYesterday we unpacked the basics of satellites and space weather. Today, we go a step further: into one of the biggest vulnerabilities facing our modern world: what happens if the Sun doesn\u2019t play along.\n\nBecause it hasn\u2019t always.\n\nSome readers might remember discussions about a \u201cGrand Solar Minimum\u201d - a quieter Sun over decades. But quiet doesn\u2019t mean harmless. The Sun doesn\u2019t switch off. It only changes its rhythm. And even during quieter periods, it can still produce sudden, powerful outbursts.\n\nFor a world that now depends on thousands of satellites moving in tight formation, it only takes one.\nRead the article here\nhttps://patriotrealm.com/4625-when-the-sun-reminds-us-whos-in-charge", "author": "Patriotrealm", "created": 1778054356088, "profile_picture": "EIlq25Xck8e3", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "When the Sun Reminds Us Who is in Charge", "last_comment_created": 1778054356088, "content": "<p>When the Sun Reminds Us Who\u2019s in Charge\nWe\u2019ve come to rely on satellites for almost everything: directions, banking, weather, communications.</p>\n<p>But all of it rests on a quiet assumption - that the Sun will behave itself.</p>\n<p>History suggests that\u2019s a risky bet.</p>\n<p>Yesterday we unpacked the basics of satellites and space weather. Today, we go a step further: into one of the biggest vulnerabilities facing our modern world: what happens if the Sun doesn\u2019t play along.</p>\n<p>Because it hasn\u2019t always.</p>\n<p>Some readers might remember discussions about a \u201cGrand Solar Minimum\u201d - a quieter Sun over decades. But quiet doesn\u2019t mean harmless. The Sun doesn\u2019t switch off. It only changes its rhythm. And even during quieter periods, it can still produce sudden, powerful outbursts.</p>\n<p>For a world that now depends on thousands of satellites moving in tight formation, it only takes one.\nRead the article here\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://patriotrealm.com/4625-when-the-sun-reminds-us-whos-in-charge\" target=\"_blank\">https://patriotrealm.com/4625-when-the-sun-reminds-us-whos-in-charge</a></p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 16, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": f